JOHANNESBURG – General Motors will no longer publish monthly vehicle sales figures in the United States, China and Brazil. The company will now issue quarterly data to the public. The automaker says the 30-day period does not accurately reflect the market. READ: Tesla overtakes General Motors in market value It will, however, continue to supply monthly data to the US Federal Reserve, industry associations and government agencies around the world. Sales were down 3, 2 percent in the US market in the first two months of 2018. eNCA